                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.113/110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName type="from"
                            >Edge</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-19T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 19, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 19—12:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>541. Your 327, September 17, 2 p.m. The French authorities have informed me
                    unofficially that France is now prepared to issue a decree reclassifying copper
                    as” a raw material just as soon as an agreement is reached between the two
                    Governments in regard to their present commercial treaty negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
